  "implemented_capabilities": [
    "Experience distillation artifact-set validator checks source intake decisions, semantic unit maps, PRD inventory rows, adoption decisions, inference records, input obligations, derived decisions, product gaps, structural reviews, and closure handoff together.",
    "Semantic units must be atomic, cite source refs, use allowed P3 semantic families, and map to existing PRD element enum values when inventory rows are created.",
    "Eligible distilled units may consume only eligible source intake items; review-required source items can preserve blockers only and rejected source items cannot feed semantic authority.",
    "Inductive candidates and product-expansion units cannot become canonical without Human Gate approval.",
    "Input obligations must route to an acquisition path or product expansion gap, and product expansion gaps cannot flow into closure as eligible units.",
    "The distill fixture consumes the approved P3 source intake fixture without changing source intake implementation artifacts.",
    "Closure handoff must cover all eligible units, all blocked semantic units, and all open product gaps before downstream closure can consume the distillation package."
  ],
